cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with tasks such as stereo matching, optical flow, and motion segmentation. The use of visual odometry also suggests a robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The fusion moves technique used for combining flow proposals could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the evaluation of the method on challenging sequences could be related to graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
